						<summary>

						<p>On a stone set up in front of the Āñjanēya temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Prabhava, Āśvija ba. 6, Tuesday.</p>						

						<p>Records the grant of land for conducting services and providing food offerings in the temple of Hanumān at Pulipāḍu by Siṅga-Paṇḍita, agent of Malika Gajasiṁvarāvu Tippanāyanigāru for the merit of his master Veligōṭi Rāyapanēniṅgāru, who was governing the <hi rend="italic">sīma.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
